Description: This R package provides a suite of helper functions designed to 
            support Bayesian Kernel Machine Regression (BKMR) analyses in 
            environmental health research. It enables users to simulate 
            realistic multivariate exposure data based on Multivariate Skewed 
            Gamma distributions, estimate distributional parameters by subgroup,
            and apply adaptive, data-driven thresholds for feature selection 
            using Posterior Inclusion Probabilities (PIPs). The package is 
            particularly useful for handling skewed exposure data and enhances 
            the interpretability of BKMR results through principled variable 
            selection.
